entries.title: Keir Starmer and Rishi Sunak clash in first U.K. election debate
entries.description: Sunak accused his challenger of not having big ideas. Starmer accused the prime minister of wanting to distance himself from the Conservative Party’s record.

entries.title: Biden announces new asylum cap in bid to deter illegal crossings
entries.description: President Biden announced a new plan to shut off access to the U.S. asylum system when illegal border crossings exceed a daily threshold.

entries.title: Biden ‘uncertain’ if Israel committing war crimes
entries.description: The U.S. leader’s remarks came as Israel signed an agreement with the United States for F-35 warplanes.

entries.title: Indian election delivers stunning setback to Modi and his party
entries.description: The BJP is still poised to form a government in coalition with allies. But this is the first time Modi has failed to win a majority over a 23-year political career.

entries.title: Who is Modi and what happened in the Indian election?
entries.description: Election results in India have not given Prime Minister Narendra Modi a predicted landslide majority. Here’s what to know about Modi and the election results so far.

entries.title: What to know about India’s election, the world’s biggest democratic event
entries.description: After 47 days of elections, Indians will get a new Parliament that the Bharatiya Janata Party is still expected to dominate.

entries.title: Why Mexico City’s thirst is causing it to sink
entries.description: The demand for water in Mexico’s capital is draining its underground aquifers — and fueling some of the fastest subsidence rates in the world.

entries.title: Netanyahu strains to keep government together amid spreading rebellions
entries.description: A string of standoffs, schisms and ultimatums have brought Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu’s emergency war cabinet to the brink of collapse.

entries.title: Netanyahu says no agreement yet on cease-fire proposal
entries.description: The Biden-led cease-fire proposal has divided public opinion in Israel, while Netanyahu and Hamas both say no agreement has yet been reached.

entries.title: Biden expected to announce new asylum restrictions at border
entries.description: President Biden is expected to announce a plan Tuesday to temporarily shut off access to the U.S.-Mexico border and restrict asylum for immigrants.

entries.title: How Mexico, bastion of machismo, got a female president before the U.S.
entries.description: The election of Claudia Sheinbaum caps a decades-long campaign for gender parity in politics, a key element of the country’s transition to democracy.

entries.title: Mexico fought for democracy. Could it slide back to a one-party state?
entries.description: The election of Claudia Sheinbaum gives the ruling Morena party the opportunity to take greater control of the federal government.

entries.title: U.S. and China lay out competing security visions for Asia-Pacific
entries.description: Speeches by Defense Secretary Lloyd Austin and Chinese counterpart Dong Jun at the Shangri-La Dialogue heavily referenced Taiwan and underscored growing U.S.-China tensions.

entries.title: OMG your hair looks so cute! Young Chinese love American ‘praise culture.’
entries.description: Even as China cools on the United States’ fashion and entertainment trends, one aspect of American life is sparking admiration: American “praise culture.”

entries.title: Russia co-opts far-right politicians in Europe with cash, officials say
entries.description: A Kremlin-backed media outlet — the Prague-based Voice of Europe — funneled hundreds of thousands of euros to far-right politicians, officials say.

entries.title: Claudia Sheinbaum elected Mexico’s first female president
entries.description: The historic vote underscored the nation’s progress on gender equity, but the Morena victory highlighted concerns about the weakening of its democratic institutions.

entries.title: Who is Claudia Sheinbaum, Mexico’s next president?
entries.description: Claudia Sheinbaum has tethered herself to the policies of her mentor, President Andrés Manuel López Obrador. How will her presidency differ from his?

entries.title: Young men flee Myanmar in panic after struggling military starts draft
entries.description: Tens of thousands have left for Thailand after Myanmar’s military, facing repeated battlefield losses, announced it aimed to conscript 60,000 soldiers.

entries.title: Zelensky comes to Asia and scolds China
entries.description: Ukraine’s president is trying to enlist leaders in Asia into a greater project of diplomacy.
